\lim_{p\rightarrow 0} \bigg[\int_{\Omega} |f|^p d\mu \bigg]^{1/p} = \exp\bigg[ \int_{\Omega} \log|f|d\mu \bigg],
(\Omega, \mathcal{F}, \mu)
f,\log |f| \in L^1(\Omega).
\int \log |f|
q
0
\int \log |f|\le \log \|f\|_q.
\int \log |f| \le \log \|f\|_q = \frac{1}{q} \log \int |f|^q \le \frac{\int (|f|^q-1)}{q}.
\|f\|_q \to \exp(\int \log |f|) \text{ as } q\to 0^+.
